snippet: Some Moroccans wonder whether the Arab Spring brought only cosmetic changes, questioning whether the king and his entourage gave up any of their power.
abstract: Growing number of Moroccans are questioning whether Arab Spring brought only cosmetic changes to their government, and whether King Mohammed VI will give up any power, despite moderate Islamist party of Prime Min Abdelilah Benkirane winning plurality in parliamentary elections. (Series: The New Islamists)
lead_paragraph: Some Moroccans wonder whether the Arab Spring brought only cosmetic changes, questioning whether the king and his entourage gave up any of their power.
